# JFTL reference test corpus — chunk 2.
# Covers source lines ~573-976: the "Builtin functions" (arithmetic, trig,
# tonumber/toboolean, add, keys...) and "User-defined functions" (def,
# closures, recursion) sections — both of which chunk 1 skipped past without
# flagging it. Continues the same ID sequence (122+) and tiering scheme as
# jftl_reference_tests_v3.txt.
#
# New this chunk: %%FAIL entries get their own tag, [NNN-fail], with JQ (the
# invalid program) and EXPECTED (jq's verbatim error text) — no INPUT (none
# in source), no JFTL/LEVEL. None found in this particular line range, but
# the convention is here for when they show up later.
#
# Same caveats as before: not engine-verified (no sandbox this session),
# best-effort tier calls given the py-tier whitelist's restrictions.


