{"main": "$pyeval=1 + float(_) + float('10')"}
}}}
COMMENT=float() isn't in the py whitelist, so eval. Also simplifies jq's tonumber (which can return int or float depending on the literal) to always-float — fine for this input, not a faithful general tonumber.

